<H3><B><I><CENTER>Part 915<BR> 
 
                 MANAGEMENT INFORMATION REPORTS
</H3></B></I></CENTER><BR><HR>
Section
915.5    Authority (Repealed)
915.10   Authority
915.20   Purpose and Scope
915.30   Definitions
915.40   Biographical Affidavits
915.50   Change in Status
915.60   Additional Information
915.70   Severability Provision
EXHIBIT A    Company Officer Appointment Form (Repealed)
<P><HR>
AUTHORITY:  Implementing Section 155.04 of the Illinois Insurance
Code (Ill. Rev. Stat. 1981, ch. 73 par. 767.4) and authorized by
Section 401 of the Illinois Insurance Code (Ill. Rev. Stat. 1981,
ch. 73, par. 1013).
<P>
SOURCE:  Standards for Formation and Management filed April 22,
1971, effective May 1, 1971; codified at 6 Ill. Reg. 12454;
amended at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983.
<P><HR><PRE><WIDTH=70>
Section 915.5  Authority (Repealed)
 
     (Source:  Repealed at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18,
         1983) 

 
Section 915.10   Authority
 
This Rule is issued by the Director of Insurance pursuant to
Section 401 of the Illinois Insurance Code (Ill. Rev. Stat. 1981,
ch. 73, par. 1013) which empowers the Director "... to make
reasonable rules and regulations as may be necessary for making
effective ..." the insurance laws of this State.

     (Source:  Former Section 915.10 repealed, new Section 915.10
         adopted at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983) 

 
Section 915.20   Purpose and Scope
 
The purpose of this Rule is to set forth requirements which the
Director deems necessary to carry out the provisions of Section
155.04 of the Illinois Insurance Code (Ill. Rev. Stat. 1981, ch.
73, par. 767.4).  The information called for by this Rule is
hereby declared to be neccessary and appropriate in the public
interest and for the protection of policyholders.  This Rule
shall apply to all domestic, foreign and alien companies licensed
to transact an insurance business in this state and to:

     a)  all persons proposing to form a domestic company under
         the laws of the State of Illinois;

     b)  all persons involved in the control, management or
         serving as an executive officer of a foreign or alien
         company applying for a Certificate of Authority to do
         business in the State of Illinois; and

     c)  all persons upon being newly elected or appointed to be
         an executive officer of any domestic, foreign or alien
         company licensed to transact an  insurance business in
         this State.

     (Source:  Former Section 915.20 repealed, new Section 915.20
         adopted at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983) 

 
Section 915.30   Definitions
 
         "Domestic, foreign or alien company" means the same as
         defined in Section 2 of the Illinois Insurance Code
         (Ill. Rev. Stat. 1981, ch. 73, par. 614).

         "Executive officer" means any person charged with active
         management and control in an executive capacity
         (including a president, vice president, treasurer,
         secretary, controller, chief actuary, general counsel,
         director, trustee, and any other person performing
         functions corresponding to those performed by the
         foregoing officers) of a company, whether incorporated
         or unincorporated.

         "Person" means natural person.

     (Source:  Former Section 915.30 repealed, new Section 915.30
         adopted at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983) 

 
Section 915.40   Biographical Affidavits
 
Biographical affidavits on the form prescribed in Illustration I,
Illinois Department of Insurance Part 913 (50 Ill. Adm. Code 913)
must be furnished to the Director by all companies and persons
subject to this Rule pursuant to Section 915.20.  Affidavits of
persons specified in Section 915.20(a) and (b) must be filed
along with the other papers and documents required for purposes
of formation of a domestic company or issuance of a Certificate
of Authority to a foreign or alien company.  Affidavits of
persons specified in Section 915.20(c) must be filed within 30
days after that persons election or appointment.  The domestic,
foreign or alien company has ultimate responsibility for timely
filing of such affidavits.

     (Source:  Former Section 915.40 repealed, new Section 915.40
         adopted at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983) 

 
Section 915.50  Change in Status
 
Domestic companies must file with the Director notice of any
change in executive officer status of any person required to file
a biographical affidavit under Section 915.40 of this Rule.
Notice must be filed within 30 days of such change.

     (Source:  Former Section 915.50 repealed, new Section 915.50
         adopted at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983) 

 
Section 915.60   Additional Information
 
The Director may request additional information such as
depositions, transcripts, reinsurance agreements, examination
reports, management and service contracts, or financial
statements as necessary to carry out the purposes of Section
155.04 of the Illinois Insurance Code.

     (Source:  Former Section 915.60 repealed, new Section 915.60
         adopted at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983) 

 
Section 915.70   Severability Provision
 
If any section or portion of a section of this rule, or the
applicability thereof to any person or circumstance is held
invalid by a court, the remainder of the rule, or the
applicability to other persons or circumstances, shall not be
effected thereby.

     (Source:  Former Section 915.70 repealed, new Section 915.70
         adopted at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18, 1983) 

 
Section 915.EXHIBIT A  Company Officer Appointment Form (Repealed)
 
     (Source:  Repealed at 7 Ill. Reg. 6939, effective May 18,
         1983) 
</PRE><P>
